SIMPLE: congelation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Congelation
<hw>Con`ge*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cong⟦eacute⟧lation</ets>, L. <ets>congelatio</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of passing, or causing to pass, from
a fluid to a solid state, as by the abstraction of heat; the act or
process of freezing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The capillary tubes are obstructed either by outward compression
or <qex>congelation</qex> of the fluid.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being congealed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is congealed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sugar plums . . . with a multitude of <qex>congelations</qex> in
jellies of various colors.</q> <rj><qau>Taller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congener</ent>⟦br⟧
